A 35-year-old suspected of house robbery and in possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition was arrested at Nzhelele Ha Rabali on Friday. Members of the Trio Task Team in the Vhembe District arrested the suspect after police received informationÂ about a house robbery in December 2022 at a farm in Musina. The police tracked down the suspects, one of them was positively identified and linked to the incident and arrested. Ammunition and 2 firearms with magazines that were reported stolen during the farm attack at Tshipise outside Musina were recovered hidden in a Kraal during the arrest. The Provincial Commissioner of the South African Police Service in Limpopo Lieutenant General Thembi Hadebe commended the members. The suspect is expected to appear in court on Monday, for unlawful possession of firearms and ammunition and house robbery. The Police investigations are still ongoing.